HEADWORD: Lardacein
<hw>Lar`da*ce"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Lardaceous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A peculiar
amyloid substance, colored blue by iodine and sulphuric acid, occurring
mainly as an abnormal infiltration into the spleen, liver,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

